title: Accident victim finds groups of men fighting over his car
text:
PETALING JAYA: A driver got out of his car after crashing it into a divider only to be greeted by a strange sight – two groups of men fighting over his vehicle. 
This bizarre scene had taken place at around 7am on Sunday when the 24-year-old man crashed his car along the LDP near Puchong. 
When he got out to survey the damage, he saw two groups of “call men” – those offering to tow and repair vehicles – in a brawl behind his car. 
Serdang OCPD Asst Comm Megat Mohamad Aminuddin Megat Alias said the situation got bloodier and stranger when another gang of men showed up in a car and attacked one of the groups with parang and sticks. 
At this point, the driver fled the scene but it did not end there as police later arrested him.
ACP Megat Mohamad Aminuddin said initial investigations led police to believe that he might have been involved in the fight somehow.
“We have arrested three people while two more are still at large.
“Four men who were slashed with parang are being treated in Serdang Hospital,” he said when contacted yesterday.
Asked if the fight could be due to business rivalry as most of those involved were “call men”, he said: “That is still under investigation but it looks more like a misunderstanding at the moment,” he said.
Those arrested have been remanded until March 6 to help in investigation.
